    "Body": " Location: San Francisco, CA Coinbase has built the world's leading compliant cryptocurrency platform serving over 30 million accounts in more than 100 countries. With multiple successful products, and our vocal advocacy for blockchain technology, we have played a major part in mainstream awareness and adoption of cryptocurrency. We are proud to offer an entire suite of products that are helping build the cryptoeconomy, and increase economic freedom around the world. There are a few things we look for across all hires we make at Coinbase, regardless of role or team. First, we assess whether a candidate demonstrates our values: Clear Communication, Positive Energy, Efficient Execution, and Continuous Learning. Second, we look for signals that a candidate will thrive in a culture like ours, where we default to trust, embrace feedback, disrupt ourselves, and expect sustained high performance because we play as a championship team. Finally, we seek people with the desire and capacity to build and share expertise in the frontier technologies of crypto and blockchain, in whatever way is most relevant to their role. Read more about our values and culture here. Crypto Team Adding crypto assets and digital currencies is core to executing on our vision and building our brand of trust. The Crypto team builds shared infrastructure to make Blockchains and Crypto assets available on Coinbase and our other business units. We take on hard engineering problems in cryptography, security, blockchain technology and distributed systems, with a focus on building high reliability services for product teams. Your Role As a Senior Engineering Manager, you will be responsible for growing and leading an engineering team towards building and maintaining the next generation of Blockchain software at Coinbase. You will be responsible for managing the architectural design and iterative implementation of highly complex, mission-critical systems. Additionally you will set and ensure reliability and service level agreements for the services that your team owns. What You\u2019ll Be Doing Leading and growing the engineering team responsible for building and maintaining Blockchain software at Coinbase. Breaking down complex projects into smaller pieces and iterating with the team on their design and implementation. Setting and maintaining Service Level Agreements and Reliability metrics for the systems that your team owns. Working closely with the Security and Infrastructure teams to ensure security and scalability of the systems that your team owns. Incident response, managing on-call rotation, and runbook creation. Project and capacity planning for your team. Mentoring Junior Engineering Managers and Tech leads. What We Look For In You 5+ years of engineering management experience. Past experience with shipping complex/multi quarter projects. Experience creating, delivering, and operating multi-tenanted, distributed systems at scale. Track record of maintaining reliability and uptime of mission critical systems. Excellent understanding of Infrastructure and Distributed system. Being able to be hands-on when needed (e.g. take on-call rotations and review projects with engineers) Ability to do both long term thinking and short term planning. Being able to balance security and usability with novel approaches to isolation and access. Computer Science degree or equivalent . Embodying our values: Positive energy, continuous learning, clear communication, efficient execution, and commitment to building an inclusive environment Nice To Haves Familiarity with Blockchains and Cryptography. Deep understanding of security best practices. Experience with Ruby or GoLang. Experience using Amazon Web Services, Lambdas, gRPC, Envoy or Kubernetes. Advanced degree (Master\u2019s and/or PhD) in math, computer science, statistics, engineering, or similar discipline. Coinbase is committed to diversity in its workforce and is proud to be an equal opportunity employer and to review all of our job postings to minimize biased language. Coinbase does not make hiring or employment decisions on the basis of race, color, religion, creed, gender, national origin, age, disability, veteran status, marital status, pregnancy, sex, gender expression or identity, sexual orientation, citizenship, or any other basis protected by applicable local, state or federal law. Coinbase will also consider for employment qualified applicants with arrest and conviction records in a manner consistent with San Francisco\u2019s Fair Chance Ordinance and similar local laws. Global Data Privacy Notice for Job Candidates and Applicants Depending on your location, the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) and California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA) may regulate the way we manage the data of job applicants. Our full notice outlining how your data will be processed as part of the application procedure for application locations is available here: Ireland/EU, United Kingdom, and California. By submitting your application, you are agreeing to our use and processing of your data as required. ", 
